        <h4 class="panel-title">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse_privacy">What about privacy ?</a>
        </h4>
      </div>
      <div id="collapse_privacy" class="panel-collapse collapse">
        <div class="panel-body">
          I care a lot about this project not being creepy : it doesn't display your name or your email, you cannot search for someone by name or get access to their email. Only github username, avatar, repository list, location, and repositories language.
          
          Though we don't display it, the database might contains informations <strong>already publicly available</strong> on your Github profile :
          <ul>
            <li>
              email
            </li>
            <li>
              Full name
            </li>
            <li>
              Location
            </li>
            <li>
              Picture (avatar)
            </li>
            <li>
              Website or blog URL
            </li>
            <li>
              Company
            </li>
          </ul>
           
           If you want to edit or remove these informations you can reach me on twitter.
        </div>
      </div>
